data.title: Royal Burial Ground, Stockholm Municipality Podcast
data.meta_description:
The Royal Cemetery is the final resting place of the Swedish royal family. Located on the island of Karlsborg in Brunnsviken Bay, it is part of Haga Park in Solna. This royal cemetery, in use since 1922, replaced the Riddarholmen Church in 1950 as the official burial site.
